@node "intro" "Introduction"

  My MultiView has configuration stored in tooltypes from version 1.5. But
configuration was very hard work so I started to write preferences program.
First versions was unusable - one have GUI, others not etc. In December 1997 
I started work on really program. First versions can only read/write
configuration but you can't change anything. I send 1st good version to Aminet
in January 1998 - it was 1.1 beta.

  Then I make many changes in code. After MultiView 4.0 release I wrote new
preferences program which can handle all MV 4.0 settings and from then prefs
program has the same version as MultiView which it can handle.

@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"

  For installation please use "Install" script supplied with MultiView 4.5 and
higher. If you want to do it by hand then just copy program to SYS:Prefs/

@endnode
@node "req" "Requirements"

  System minimum is :

   2.04   - to run

  Requied libraries :

   FileID.library       v.2+    (included with MultiView)
   Asl.library          v.38+   (part of AmigaOS)

@endnode
@node "Usage" "Usage"

  Just run it - it will read SYS:Utilities/Multiview icon.

@endnode
